post_text: The Spurettes finished up their summer strength and conditioning today. I wish I could tell you how proud I am of them! They’ve done a great job of being committed and wanting to better themselves. The strength they have gained is crazy! I know they have lifted more than they ever thought they could and it’s was awesome to see! Sports are so much more than winning and losing. It’s bettering yourself as a person, battling through hard times, and being apart of a TEAM! I’m excited that school is starting and we get to continue to love on your kids and push them to be the best! There’s not a better group of girls out there! Very proud of the Spurettes! Let’s have a great year!

If we get the okay in the coming weeks and have been on the couch and are out of shape then we have hurt our chances. I will post the workouts here as well. I have asked the kids to tag me on Instagram, Facebook, or twitter with a picture or video of their workout. post_text:
Our Varsity XC kids did a great job today in Wichita Falls this morning.

Our varsity girls did phenomenal. The Spurettes finished 2nd overall as team. We had 5 girls medal in the top 25! That’s great! They competed so well today! Bucki finished 2nd overall.

I moved the varsity boys up a division to compete against the 5A/6A runners. They finished 4th out of 8 teams against schools with 10X our enrollment. Proud of the way they competed today!! They all did awesome! Jorden finished 2nd overall with a PR of 16:26

Spurettes: (100 total runners)
Bucki - 2nd (medalist)
Cara - 14th (medalist)
Paige - 16th (medalist)
Brianna - 17th (medalist)
Alyssa - 24th (medalist)
Ravaya - 28th
Abby - 31st

Bulldogs:
Jorden - 2nd (medalist)
Zage - 19th (medalist)
Luke - 32nd
Craig - 34th
Zek - 44th
Wyatt - 45th
Eoin - 51st
Liam - 53rd

post_text:
Proud of our Bulldogs, Bullpups, & Spurettes today. They survived the hot and humid day in Haskell and competed well! It was our JH’s first meet of the year and they did great for the first one of the year!! JH Spurettes team consisted of Allee Hamilton, Emily Swaringen, Macye Maben, Tory Childers, & Tatum Walker. The Bullpups were Erik Molina, JD Hamilton, Haden Carrillo, Preston Abbott. A couple of highlights, Erik Molina finished 11th and Allee Hamilton finished 17th. Our Varsity Bulldogs finished 4th as a team on a crazy course! Jorden Zarate finished 1st overall! Our Varsity Spurettes finished 3rd overall out of 11teams. Majority had :45 sec to 1:30 min taken off of their time from last week. That’s fantastic!

Varsity Bulldogs (Top 5):
Jorden 1st
Craig 23rd
Wyatt 31st
Garrett 43rd
Wylie 49th

Varsity Spurette (Top 5):
Bucki 10th
Tristen 12th
Cara 19th
Paige 31st
Ravaya 57th

A great way to start the year for our XC teams! They ran a tough, hot course this morning in Midland and did great! Boys team finished 4th out of 19 teams 1A-4A. That’s great! A couple of highlights: Jorden Zarate finished 1st overall and Zage Barron was also a medalist finishing 18th. Spurettes ran a great first race of the season this morning! They finished 3rd overall out of 20 teams 1A-4A. A couple of highlights: Bucki Smith 8th medalist and Tristen Martin 9th medalist.

Parents, we mailed out physical paperwork and drug testing paperwork today for all of our 7th-12th grade athletes. You will be able to go down to our local clinic and get it done. 7th, 9th, & 11th graders will need to get their physicals.

8th, 10th, & 12th graders will only need to fill out their medical history, but they DO NOT have to get a new physical. Of course, everyone will need to fill out and return ALL paperwork.

Our initial mandatory Drug Testing for EVERYONE WHO COMPETES IN EXTRACURRICULAR ACTIVITIES will be on Tuesday, July 30th at 5:30 pm. We will have our Parent/Athlete meeting in the Old Gym prior to start of our Drug Testing.

If at all possible, we would like to have all paperwork turned at the meeting on July 30th. Summer is winding down. We look forward to another GREAT year. Go Bulldogs and Spurettes!
